Figures 15 & 17
). Labrum with six pairs of dorsal setae, all of moderate length except for elongated M 3 and La 2 ; venter of labrum with three pairs of epipharyngeal setae, the two mesal setae only slightly longer than lateral seta (
Figures 18–19
